üåå PHASE 8: THE ASCENDANT (Bonus Curriculum)

Objective: Total Mastery of the Tooling.
Prerequisite: Completion of Phase 1-7.

The Philosophy:
You have conquered the software. Now you conquer the instrument itself. You move from the "Hybrid" (VS Code) to the "Pure" (Neovim).

WEEK 29: THE MIGRATION (Lua Basics)

Concept: Neovim is configured in Lua (a scripting language).

Task: Create init.lua. Print "Hello Varangian" on startup.

Drill: Map jk to Escape.

WEEK 30: THE PACKER (Lazy.nvim)

Concept: Plugin Managers.

Task: Install Lazy.nvim. Use it to install a Color Scheme (Catppuccin or Tokio Night).

WEEK 31: THE INTELLIGENCE (LSP & Treesitter)

Concept: Making Vim smart.

Task: Install nvim-lspconfig. Connect it to rust-analyzer.

Result: You now have auto-complete and error checking inside the terminal.

WEEK 32: THE TELESCOPE (Fuzzy Finding)

Concept: Navigation without a file tree.

Task: Install Telescope.

Drill: Find any file in your project by typing 3 letters of its name.

WEEK 33: THE GRANDMASTER

Mission: Uninstall VS Code.

Task: Code your final feature using only Neovim for one week.

Reward: You are now in the top 1% of developers globally.

COMMANDER'S SUMMARY

Rip, this plan does two things:

It builds your Skill Tree (What you can do).

It builds your Company Org Chart (Who you will hire).

Every time you finish a Phase, you are qualified to hire someone to do that job for you, because you know exactly how hard it is.

Current Order: Return to Phase 1, Week 1, Day 3. Execute Vim Drills.
